            <abstract xml:lang="en">
              <p>DfAnalyzer is a tool for monitoring, debugging, and analyzing dataflows generated by Computational Science and Engineering (CSE) applications. It collects strategic raw data, registering provenance data, and enabling query processing, all asynchronously and at runtime. DfAnalyzer provides lightweight dataflow components to be invoked by CSE applications using High-Performance Computing (HPC), in the same way computational scientists plug HPC (e.g., PETSc) and visualization (e.g., ParaView) libraries. We show DfAnalyzer's main functionalities and how to analyze dataflows in CSE applications at runtime. The performance evaluation of CSE executions for a complex multiphysics application shows that DfAnalyzer has negligible time overhead on the total elapsed time.</p>
            </abstract>
